<para id="fs-id1165036842387"><emphasis effect="bold">Check Your Understanding</emphasis> One end of a 3.0-m rope is tied to a tree; the other end is tied to a car stuck in the mud. The motorist pulls sideways on the midpoint of the rope, displacing it a distance of 0.25 m. If he exerts a force of 200.0 N under these conditions, determine the force exerted on the car.</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1165036787956">
<para id="fs-id1165036787958"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>6.0</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> N</para>
</solution>
