</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1165038304565">
<problem id="fs-id1165038304567">
<para id="fs-id1165038304569">What force must be applied to a 100.0-kg crate on a frictionless plane inclined at <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>30</m:mn><m:mtext>°</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> to cause an acceleration of <m:math><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mn>2.0</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>m/s</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> up the plane?</para>
<media id="fs-id1165038304591" alt="Figure shows an object on a slope of 30 degrees. An arrow pointing up and parallel to the slope is labeled F.">
